description: Demolish existing structures. Redevelopment of retail warehouse for mixed use development comprising 7 buildings. Provision of flexible use space (Use Class E/F1) at ground and first floor (Class E/F1). Creation of up to 568 residential units with associated public space, private landscaped amenity spaces, ancillary car parking and cycle and refuse stores. (Summary).
decision_conditions:
Prior to the commencement of  the relevant  Phase identified on the Phasing Plan submitted under condition 3 above (excluding site clearance, demolition and preparatory construction works), details of the following shall be submitted to approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority:
a.	long and short stay cycle parking for the commercial users. The cycle parking details shall demonstrate how the designs are to be in accordance with the London Cycling Design Standards. 
b.	Details of the sustainable transport hub space, cycle maintenance infrastructure and air pump contained within
c.	Brompton, other portable bicycle, cargo (larger) and electric bicycle hire storage locations and parking space for returns

The cycle parking and infrastructure supporting bike hire hereby approved shall be installed as per the approved details and retained, not used for any other purpose and be maintained in good working order.

Reason: To ensure appropriate support facilities for cyclists are provided in the scheme and to comply with policy T5 of the London Plan.
